    "### 6.3 Model Selection & Justification\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Neural Network (MLP, tuned via GridSearchCV)** achieved the highest AUC and is selected as the best model for predicting rain tomorrow. However, the Logistic Regression performed very similarly and offers greater interpretability — making it a strong choice where explainability matters.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.4 Positives and Negatives of Each Method\n",
    "\n",
    "**Decision Tree**\n",
    "- ✅ Easy to interpret and visualise\n",
    "- ✅ No feature scaling required\n",
    "- ✅ Handles both numeric and categorical features\n",
    "- ❌ Prone to overfitting without tuning\n",
    "- ❌ Sensitive to small changes in data\n",
    "- ❌ Can develop bias as tree depth increases\n",
    "\n",
    "**Logistic Regression**\n",
    "- ✅ Highly interpretable coefficients\n",
    "- ✅ No overfitting observed\n",
    "- ✅ Robust and fast to train\n",
    "- ❌ Assumes linear relationship between features and log-odds\n",
    "- ❌ Requires feature scaling\n",
    "- ❌ Limited by its linear decision boundary\n",
    "\n",
    "**Neural Network (MLP)**\n",
    "- ✅ Highest AUC — best discriminatory power\n",
    "- ✅ Captures non-linear relationships\n",
    "- ✅ Flexible architecture via tuning\n",
    "- ❌ Less interpretable (\"black box\")\n",
    "- ❌ Requires careful tuning to avoid overfitting\n",
    "- ❌ Slower to train; sensitive to feature scaling"
   ]
