    "## Final Thoughts\n",
    "\n",
    "This project explored three classification approaches for predicting next-day rainfall using 10 years of BOM weather data across 49 Australian locations. Key takeaways:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Humidity3pm** was consistently the most important predictor across all model types — high afternoon humidity is the strongest signal for next-day rain.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Hyperparameter tuning is essential.** The default decision tree overfit catastrophically; GridSearchCV resolved this across all models.\n",
